How have they evolved the prices of the trips since 1989
Until 1989 there were in the Czechoslovakia of then alone five authorized state travel agencies: Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autoturist.
The travel agencies of that moment sold in most cases travel alone to the socialist block, therefore the trips to West were very restricted.
The Czech tourists went, therefore, of holidays to the beaches of the REV (German Democratic Republic), to the Soviet Union, (Sochi in Crimea in the Black Sea) to Bulgaria and Romania (both in the Black Sea) and to Hungary (Balaton).
A positive exception was the period understood between 1962 and 1972, when could travel to Yugoslavia, nevertheless, later the Yugoslavian state inclined toward the west and the trips of the Czech tourists were then enough restricted.
A great paradox of the socialism was the fact that to the citizens of the socialist block (that is to say, also to the Checoeslovacos) be not to permitted them to travel free and individually not even by the socialist countries.
If a citizen wanted to travel individually, for example, to Poland or to the Soviet Union, needed a letter of invitation, if not, the individual trip was not possible.
The travel agencies offered in those times also travel to the West, but one should be put to the queue with a bag to sleep and to pass thus all the night, or to have "good acquaintances" in the agency.
Even so not all was earned.
The call "promise of change" that was the condition for the trips to the West, itself was not granted to the "reliable politically little people", that thus could not travel at all.
The czechoslovakian currency was not a freely convertible currency and, unsecured of change, was not possible to obtain the resources (the western currency) to travel to West.
The great majority of the Czechs they passed their holidays in their own country, for which there was a great number of cabins and summer homes, that the Czechs acquired. This custom still persists.
The way to travel from the Czechs has suffered since 1989 an authentic revolution.
While until 1989 for us was the does not go more to spend the holiday in the REV or Bulgaria, last year the Czechs did 4.5 million trips of holidays to countries of the entire world.
It results nna great paradox, of the one that nowadays no longer we are conscious, the fact that to the at present favorite destiny, Croatia, until 1989 could not travel itself freely, because formed part of the Yugoslavia of then.
At the beginning of the years 90 the exemption of visas was imposed to travel to the neighboring States of Europe western, what caused an enormous wave of visits of short term, above all to Vienna or Germany.
The checoeslovacos, for a long time, himself not enough of the excursions to the West were seen, everyone he wanted to see the him less for a moment.
For example, in Paris the groups of Czechs in the parks in tents slept, since our incomes of then us did not permit to pay a hotel or pension.
A typical characteristic of the Czechs of that time was it to be carried with himself the food (preserves, stuffed, etc.) to save.
Another important moment was the introduction of the convertibility of the Czech crown, thus our tourists were able finally, after decades, to buy freely western currency.
Our standard of living enlarged and with him also the salaries media, what around 1997 caused an increase in the demand of trips.
With the increase of the demand of trips they began the agencies, from 1997 with regularity, to prepare the trips using the connections of charter flights, what caused descended incredibly the prices of the trips in comparison with the past, thanks to the possibility of obtaining discounts by the volume of passengers.
To ends from the 90 of last century, already the Czechs travelled without visa to almost all the countries developed, except United States, which simplified still more our trips.
Another interesting moment in the history of the pursuit-revolutionary tourism happened already in the 2000, when was organized, thanks to an enormous demand, the first flight direct from Chequia to an exotic country, and went to Thailand.
Since that year, leave every year direct charter flights with Czech tourists did warm and distant countries. This winter already will fly directly from Chequia to 12 exotic destinies.
The exotic countries visit them at present near 100 thousand Czechs to the year.
Another interesting moment of this epoch, that symbolizes our pursuit-revolutionary development, arrived in the year 2008.
November 17, 2008, United States eliminated the visas for the Czech tourists, with what our country passed to be among the most developed countries of the world.
In 2008 the Czechs, for the first time in their history, they have passed more than the half of their holidays abroad (50,3%) and for the first time in their history, they have been spent in trips abroad more than 15 thousand Czech crowns by head, including the expenses in the place of stay.
