Cross López explained that three main components exist that cause excess, obesity and other chronic sufferings: the sedentary lifestyle, that is the lack of daily physical activity, to remain most of the seated day set against the television set and to utilize media of transportation instead of walking short distances.
Also itself due to the high caloric consumption, that is to say, the major consumption of sweet beverages, of carbohydrates (tamales, bread, pizza, hamburger, etc) with high content in greases and proteins and the genetics that is analyzed in this protocol.
Asphalt of the UNAM would avoid potholes
Rafael Blacksmith, investigator of the Faculty of Chemistry of the UNAM, develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a mixture with better performance, independently of the environmental conditions and of temperature
If the signs that sends the pavement to be attended, would not be necessary to repair near 200 thousand potholes each season of rains in the Metropolitan Zone of the Valley of Mexico, notified Rafael Blacksmith Nájera, investigator of the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, who assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of a pavement asfáltico is the adequate one, the potholes would be able to be reduced in quantity or, even, to be eliminated for Complete.
In its conference A technological opinion of the potholes, dictation in the framework of the International Year of the Chemistry, brought to light that the laboratory to its charge develops asphalts modified with polymers to produce a mixture with similar characteristics to those of the asphalt, but with a greater so much, mechanical resistance to high as to low temperatures.
Blacksmith Nájera reckoned that this type of asphalts modified they would be able to be utilized in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some north cities of the country, to improve its performance and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
It explained that the asphalt, the heaviest part of the petroleum, is a hydrocarbons molecules assembly, some of highly molecular weight, calls pave us, and other of low molecular weight, calls maltenos, that you join they give to the pavement their characteristic behavior viscoelástico.
The behavior viscoelástico of the asphalt consists of that to high temperatures, near the 180 degrees, behaves as a liquid, to 120 degrees centigrade its viscosity is very high and to 50 degrees centigrade presents an almost solid state, while to very low temperatures, the asphalt returns fragile, added.
The previous thing signifies that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform, but goes modifying during the day according to the environmental conditions and of temperature, notified the specialist in chemical engineering.
The investigator of the FQ observed that the streets of Mexico City mostly are covers by flexible pavement, which is composed of six layers of materials, of which the last three involve to the asphalt.
Among the most superficial layers the folder is found asfáltica, conformed by small stones bathed in asphalt and then compacted.
Each one of the stones that constitutes the folder, aimed, is bathed with asphalt.
Upon traveling the vehicles and to be generated efforts, this permits that the forces be diffused very well in the pavement.
If it was a matter of asphalt modified they would be diffused still better, the chemical engineer thought.
On the folder asfáltica, abounded, a last layer is placed called folder of tread, which is made of a material of fine stone, that is to say, a sand that also bathes in asphalt.
As it is a matter of the layer that is going to be in contact with the rims of the vehicles, should have more forces mechanical that the folder asfáltica and to provide friction on the road.
Upon being the part of the pavement that is going to receive and to diffuse the efforts, the folder of tread requires, likewise, to have the adequate thickness and the material of the one should take care of itself that is done.
The climate, especially the humidity and the variations of temperature, also they are a very important factor to consider, especially the water, he said, because affects considerably the performance of the folder asfáltica.
When the land is dampened, the water is diffused in the interior of the folder and is difficult that leave, this causes a softening of all the layers of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
In the process of formation of a pothole, he said, the first one in being eroded is the movie of running and only later the folder is affected asfáltica, but the damage does not occur instantly, but is a process that should be attended to the first signs with adequate programs of maintenance.
The also member of the National System of Investigators explained that the traffic load is another important factor in the formation of potholes and, because of it, the thickness of each one of the layers of the pavement should go always in relation to the traffic load and to guarantee that comply, to avoid that potholes be formed often.
Rafael Blacksmith notified that still there is a lot that to investigate and to work on the asphalt, for example, the emulsions asfálticas, that in other countries already they are found even in the market and they permit to repair the potholes with facility and without high need to use temperatures.
