The question is that, on this theme, there is enough consensus between the left and the right.
In the case of the right, Jacques Chirac set the orientation declaring in 1976 that "900,000 unemployed should not be a problem for a country that counts on near two million immigrant workers", while in the left, the tone set it Michel Rocard explaining that France "cannot be takes charge of all the misery of the world" in 1990.
