The Nord Stream, new door of entrance of the Russian gas in Europe
The gas pipeline Nord Stream, that communicates directly Europe western with Russia passing for the Baltic bottom of the sea, already has itself placed in service.
It should supply gas to satisfy the needs of thirty million homes.
Gazprom, the Russian giant of the gas, has wanted to celebrate the event with great pomp.
Last Tuesday, more than 500 guests, included four Heads of state and of Government, they participated on the banks of the Baltic one, between the music of the orchestra and a delicate buffet, in the inauguration of the Nord Stream, the new gas pipeline that communicates directly, under the sea, Russia with Germany.
Symbolically, the German Chancellor Angela Merkel, the Russian President Dmitri Medvedev, the French prime Minister François Fillon and their counterpart of the Netherlands, Mark Rutte, they have rotated together the steering wheel of the valve that controls the entrance of Russian gas in the network of Europe western.
With this new gas pipeline, each year 27.5 million cubic meters of additional Russian gas to Europe western through a first one will arrive had of 1,224 km that communicate the region of San Petersburgo with the Land of Mecklemburgo-Pomerania.
A second pipe should be concluded by the end of 2012 that will permit to supply a total of 55,000 million cubic meters of gas, that is to say, sufficient to cover all the French consumption.
Besides, already it is spoken of the possibility to build a third pipe by the same one traveled through.
For Gazprom, the finalización to time of this enormous work presents air of victory.
Poland and the Baltic countries had opposed firmly to the project.
In fact, the Nord Stream is going to permit to supply gas directly to Germany, avoiding the terrestrial course by third parties countries (Poland and Ukraine).
Of blow, these two countries lose something of its power: for them, will be more difficult to influence in Russia threatening to close him the access to the markets of Europe western.
In the climactic point of the debate, Warsaw did not doubt in comparing the Nord Stream as a "new German-Soviet pact", in reference to the alliance between Hitler and Stalin to occupy Poland in 1939.
That is to say, if the theme is politically delicate.
Europe western, supporting the Russian project, has obtained a greater security of supply.
But the price is a weakening of the Europe of the energy, given that the project has generated a gap between the Europeans of the east and of the west.
Russia has known, in so alone five years, to cause to succeed its vision of a direct alliance between Russia and the countries western rich, large consumers of gas and with some reserves each more limited time.
"This gas pipeline constitutes a component of our association with Russia, a new artery that unites us of organic form", confirmed François Fillon during the inauguration of the gas pipeline, showing up to what point the large contracts of the sector of the gas are as political as economic.
All this explains the extensive smiles in the faces of the executives of Gazprom, numerous in Lubmin, in the point of arrival of the gas.
The construction of this gas pipeline also supposes a technical achievement.
The underwater pipe is manufactured of steel covered of cement to protect it against the anchors of the ships.
It is supported in the bottom of the sea, to an average of 200 m of depth.
Build it, was necessary to avoid fields of mines that date from World War Two.
"It was necessary to withdraw or to destroy about a hundred them, by precaution", indicates Jens Müller, spokesman of the company Nord Stream.
Likewise, turned out to be necessary to maximize the measures of protection of the fauna and the flora.
The pipe is a long snake of metal that weighs as 242 towers Eiffel and is not interrupted in all its length: neither by valves, neither by stations of maintenance.
It was predicted a platform of control in the water of Sweden, but the responsible for the project they renounced the same one upon seeing that the Swedes were not very willing to permit that a Russian state company be to established of permanent form in the sea set against their coasts.
"In case of damage, we will interrupt the step of the gas in less than one minute", I need Jens Müller.
In case of leak, the gas of the gas pipeline will free, therefore, to the atmosphere.
But the builders consider little probable that a leak be produced, since have predicted junctures that, according to the forecasts, they will have a leak each 100,000 years.
The control of the state of the gas pipeline is guaranteed by means of an underwater robot, dragged by a ship, that carries out exterior inspections, as well as by means of a device that circulates for the interior of the gas pipeline.
With the form of a pure one, is introduced in the interior of the pipe, that possesses a diameter of a meter, and moves with the gas.
To its arrival, after three complete days of trip to a velocity of three meters by second, supplies precise data on possible deformations of the metal.
The gas pipeline has been designed to function for fifty years without repair any type need.
The circulation of the gas is guaranteed simply by the pressure.
At the beginning is of 200 bars and, on the way out of 100 bars.
Five businesses have united their forces to be able to carry out this project.
The business leader is Gazprom, that possesses the 51% of the participations.
To her, united the Germans AND.ON and BASF (15.5% each one), as well as the Dutch one Gasunie and the French group GDF Suez (9% each one).
These five companies have created a common business, call Nord Stream, responsible for building and to exploit the gas pipeline.
Has its headquarters in Zoug, Swiss, where the imposition turns out to be especially favorable.
Later, Gazprom rented to said company, during a time limit of twenty-five renewable years, the totality of the gas transportation capacities.
"To Gazprom will pay him for the total capacity, independently of the quantity of gas that really himself transportation", I need Jens Müller.
The financing of the construction of the gas pipeline has been carried I finish in a 30% with the contribution of the shareholders and in a 70% by means of bank loans.
The total price of the work should reach 7,400 million euro for the two pipes.
For GDF Suez, for example, the investment has reached the 240 million.
But the minority shareholders are sure that they will not surpass its investment, since Gazprom assumes in and of itself the risk of the expenses.
The gas pipeline emerges of the Baltic one in Lubmin, in a sandy coast planted of pines.
Some valves, with 4.5 meters of height, they form the door at the outset of the gas.
Some sensors exist that measure the pressure, the temperature and the specific characteristics of the gas to the arrival, before be transfered to the German gas pipelines.
Since last Tuesday, the terminal receives a million cubic meters of Russian gas each hour.
To total capacity, they will be three million for hour and in 2012, six million.
